What CHANGES between problems — just 3 things
-------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Return type of union()
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Return boolean only when you need to detect cycles or new connections. Otherwise void is fine.

-------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Rank Optimisation:
-------------------------------------------------------------------
// Without rank (simpler, slightly slower). Rank just keeps the tree balanced.
parent[px] = py; // just pick one

// With rank (faster, union by rank)
if (rank[px] < rank[py])      
    parent[px] = py;
else if (rank[px] > rank[py]) 
    parent[py] = px;
else{ 
    // Make x new parent and increment its rank
    parent[py] = px; 
    rank[px]++; 
}

